column5: yup its that time of the year that i only have a few more outings left of the season for musky so im gonna make my end of year review now i started the season off fishing for walleye and did we ever do good with many day caching 20-30 fish deffinitly my best year for walleye yet        then i started out the bass season on good hands with the pro am   more random bass of the season            '      bass seasone was very short for me because this year i was determand to catch a musky and low and behold i did  8)   my first brooky was also caught on my vacation to nova scotia   and my biggest   also caught my uglyest fish ever   also got a couple bigger "junk fish" in the season not the targets but still fun     yup lots of pix hope you all enjoyed though and have a good end to your softwater season  8)
sweet !!! what the heck is that ugly thing.Kinda looks like a goby of sorts.
That is a scalpin my first and only saltwater fish really turned me off from ocean fishing after that haha
nice report ... but why when you guy's hold up the little ones, theres no smiles?
Good season indeed. Nothing wrong with a few kitties man...they fight and taste good. That musky is a b-youttie.
We caught a few of those sculpin when we were out on the Bay Of Fundy a couple years ago. I think I had a flounder but I lost it before I got it to the boat. I take it you never got any flounder?

Sculpin are in freshwater too. We caught quite a few of them when we were smelt fishing. They will swim up the creeks in the spring to feed on the smelt eggs. They look nearly identical to the ones in your photo.
Great Report very nice variety, congrats on the Musky & I wouldn't be putting the Pike down as Junk fish myself, but to each their own Richard
I noticed that the biggest smile was with the biggest Walleye  Looks like you had a great year. Fishing is like a fine wine - it gets better with age so keep on fishin' !
Looks like a very productive season. You guys in Ottawa have some great fishing over there! Thanks for sharing.
Looks like you had a good season. Quite a mix.  Keep it up.  Chad
That's quite the mix of species for one season.  Congrates on a great year!!
